---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<div
		class="header"
		role="presentation"
	>
		<h1>Carrie Ryan</h1>
		<i>Front-End Engineer</i>
	</div>
	<div
		class="content-container"
		role="presentation"
	>
		<section class="experience-section">
			<h2>Experience</h2>

			<Card
				title="Concord Direct"
				subtitle="Senior Front-End Software Engineer | Technical Lead"
				location="Concord, NH (Remote)"
				date="2023-present"
			>
				<p>
					Lead front-end engineer advising nonprofit organizations on technical
					best practices for accessibility, architecture and security. Leading a
					team of 4 in creating and maintaining modern web applications for
					clients. Mentoring junior and mid-level engineers by advising on
					modern front-end practices and creating front-end training resources.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<b>Data Reporting Application</b> - Created an application for Concord
						Direct's business intelligence team. The application ensures clean data
						is provided to all client reports, which decreases turnaround time by
						an average of 50%.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>A/B Testing</b> - Researched, advised, integrated and trained Concord
						Direct's largest digital services client on A/B testing. The A/B testing
						tool was integrated into 2 of the client's highest trafficked websites.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>JAMstack Pivot</b> - In a team of 3, transitioned Concord Direct's
						leading client from 15 Wordpress sites to JAMstack websites with a headless
						CMS. The switch increased accessibility and page speed scores, and resolved
						all flagged security vulnerabilities.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Card>
			<Card
				title="Embrace Pet Insurance"
				subtitle="Front-End Software Engineer | Team Lead"
				location="Cleveland, OH"
				date="2019 - 2023"
			>
				<p>
					Supported the company’s website and 3 customer-facing applications.
					Led a team of 6 through the project lifecycle, including gathering
					project requirements and leading all Scrum events.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<b>Policy Restructure</b> - Led a team of 6 in adding new policy options
						to all internal and external applications. Responsibilities included
						gathering requirements and writing user stories; leading team through
						Scrum events; teaching team to use new work management software, Jira.
						Sole front-end developer on project to update all internal and external
						applications.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>Embrace Pet Insurance Rebrand</b> - Main point of contact for contractors
						working on the company’s customer-facing applications. Created documentation,
						trained contractors in Embrace’s code standards and performed code reviews.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>Website Migration</b> - In a team of 3, transitioned customer-facing
						website to headless CMS. Built web scraping tool to migrate 95% of website
						data to new site. Gathered requirements and created user stories; wrote
						documentation for best practices and code standards; and performed code
						reviews.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>Quote Engine Revamp</b> - In a team of 6, modernized the entire tech
						stack of our policy purchase application. Converted the front-end from
						AngularJS to Angular. Integrated Google Tag Manager and Google Analytics
						into the new application.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Card>

			<Card
				title="Emerson"
				subtitle="Software Developer"
				location="Berea, OH"
				date="2018 - 2019"
			>
				<p>
					Contributed to Emerson’s Commercial Residential web development team
					as both a front-end .NET developer and Scrum Master. Involved in the
					full lifecycle of development, including scoping out project
					requirements, writing tickets and quality assurance.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<b>Klauke Website Migration</b> - In a team of 6, migrated over customer,
						media and product data to a new CMS platform. Gathered requirements and
						led the team through Scrum events, including sprint planning and retrospective.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>Greenlee Website Migration</b> - Created a new user interface that
						follows Emerson’s stylistic standards. Migrated over media and product
						data to the new Emerson CMS platform. Scrum Master for a team of 6.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Card>

			<Card
				title="United Consumer Financial Services"
				subtitle="Full-Stack Developer"
				location="Westlake, OH"
				date="2017 - 2018"
			>
				<p>
					Contributed to the design, development, testing, maintenance and
					enhancement of UCFS’s ASP.NET and .NET Core MVC web applications. Also
					contributing to data warehousing and computer networking projects.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<b>Personal Loan Application</b>- Developed a responsive web
						application in a team of 3 for UCFS’s leading client. The
						application allows customers to apply for a loan online and receive
						immediate feedback on their application.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>Distributor Application</b> - Created a responsive web application
						in a team of 2. The application allows a new potential distributor interested
						in partnering with UCFS to apply online rather than the current paper
						application.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Card>
		</section>

		<section class="education-section">
			<h2>Education</h2>
			<Card
				title="We Can Code IT"
				subtitle="Software Engineering Certificate"
				location="Cleveland, OH"
